## Key Platform Concepts

### Organization & Auth
- **Organization ID**: unique identifier for your Coveo org (e.g. `roelc_pokemon`)
- **API Key**: for local dev, use an **Anonymous Search** template API key. Never expose keys tagged "Must remain private"
- **Search Token**: server-issued token recommended for production; not implemented in this scaffold (deliberate — see `docs/design-decisions.md` DD-3)

### Sources
- **Web (cloud crawler) source**: this project uses one named `PokemonDB Crawl`. URL rules restrict it to `/pokedex/{slug}` species pages and exclude `/move/`, `/moves/`, `/type/`, `/ability/`, `/item/`, `/mechanic/`, `/pokebase/`, `/evolution/`
- **Push source**: alternative — not used here
- **Tip**: create a second source pointing only at `https://pokemondb.net/pokedex/bulbasaur` for fast scrape/selector iteration without recrawling the full dex

### Web Scraping Configuration
- Attached to a Web source; controls what metadata is extracted from each crawled page
- Uses **jsoup-flavored CSS selectors** plus Coveo's `::text` and `::attr(...)` pseudo-elements
- **Stick to standard CSS3** where possible — `:has()` / `:matchesOwn()` have produced asymmetric failures in this project (see `docs/coveo-admin-playbook.md` §1 "Selector style rejected"). Position-anchored `:nth-of-type` plus a unique-ID anchor (e.g. `#dex-stats`) is the proven-stable style
- Attach in Coveo Admin Console: Sources → your source → **Web Scraping**

### Fields (current schema for this project)

Custom fields live in Admin → Content → Fields. **All shipped:**

| Field | Type | Facet | Multi-value | Sortable | Source data |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| `pokemontype` | String | Yes | Yes | No | Type icons in Pokédex data table |
| `pokemongeneration` | String | Yes | No | No | `<abbr>` in intro paragraph |
| `pokemonability` | String | Yes | Yes | No | `a[href^="/ability/"]` links |
| `pictureuri` | String | No | No | No | `<meta property="og:image">` |
| `pokemonbst` | Integer 32 | Yes (auto) | No | Yes (auto) | Base Stats table → Total cell |
| `pokemonhp` | Integer 32 | Yes (auto) | No | Yes (auto) | Base Stats table → HP row |
| `pokemonattack` | Integer 32 | Yes (auto) | No | Yes (auto) | Base Stats table → Attack row |
| `pokemondefense` | Integer 32 | Yes (auto) | No | Yes (auto) | Base Stats table → Defense row |
| `pokemonspatk` | Integer 32 | Yes (auto) | No | Yes (auto) | Base Stats table → Sp. Atk row |
| `pokemonspdef` | Integer 32 | Yes (auto) | No | Yes (auto) | Base Stats table → Sp. Def row |
| `pokemonspeed` | Integer 32 | Yes (auto) | No | Yes (auto) | Base Stats table → Speed row |

- **Integer 32** is what trial orgs offer (Long isn't exposed). For Pokémon stats (max ~720) it's wildly sufficient.
- Coveo **auto-locks** Facet=Yes, Sortable=Yes, Multi-value=No when you pick Integer 32 — no manual toggling needed.
- Per-stat fields are unused by the UI today (only `pokemonbst` is faceted) but kept in the index for future sorting (`buildSort`), ranking expressions (`@pokemonspeed>=120^15`), and per-stat facets.
- Default fields: `title`, `uri`, `clickUri`, `date`, `filetype`, `language` (auto-populated, no schema work).

### Facets
- A field must exist in the index AND be marked **Facet: Yes** in Admin to be facetable
- Multi-value fields (e.g. `pokemontype`, `pokemonability`) need **Multi-value facet: Yes** so each value gets its own bucket
- Numeric facets (`buildNumericFacet`) use **range buckets**, not discrete values; the BST facet defines five labeled tiers in `BST_TIERS` in `web/src/coveo/search-instance.ts`

### Machine Learning models (all live)
- **`pokemon_QS`** — Query Suggestions, associated to default pipeline; status: Limited until traffic accumulates
- **`pokemon_RGA`** — Relevance Generative Answering, associated; status: Active
- **`pokemon_ART`** — Automatic Relevance Tuning, associated; status: Build in progress (training on `documentClick` events from `buildInteractiveResult`)
- Optional warm-up: `tools/seed-ml/` Playwright runner (`npm run seed` from that folder)

### Search API
- Endpoint: `https://platform.cloud.coveo.com/rest/search/v2` (US region)
- All queries route through the **default Query Pipeline** which holds: Featured Result rules (Pikachu/starter pins), and the three ML model associations above
- The detail page (`web/src/coveo/fetch-pokemon-by-slug.ts`) calls this endpoint directly with `analytics: { enabled: false }` so detail-page fetches don't pollute search analytics

