## pokemondb.net Structure (verified May 2026)
- Individual Pokémon pages: `https://pokemondb.net/pokedex/{name}` — **INCLUDE** these (one path segment after `/pokedex/`)
- Multi-segment paths (`/pokedex/game/...`, `/pokedex/stats/...`) — EXCLUDE
- Hub pages (`/pokedex/all`, `/pokedex/national`) — typically excluded except when used as starting URL
- Other site sections — EXCLUDE: `/move/`, `/moves/`, `/type/`, `/ability/`, `/item/`, `/mechanic/`, `/pokebase/`, `/evolution/`
- **Image**: `<meta property="og:image">` is the most stable extractor
- **Type(s)**: first `table.vitals-table` ("Pokédex data") → Type row → `a.type-icon` links
- **Generation**: `<abbr>` element in the intro paragraph (NOT in the vitals table — many Pokémon lack a Generation row in vitals)
- **Abilities**: `a[href^="/ability/"]` links in Pokédex data table (multi-value, semicolon-joined)
- **Base Stats**: `<table class="vitals-table">` nested under `#dex-stats ~ div.resp-scroll`; stat rows in `<tbody>`, Total in `<tfoot>`
- **Multi-form Pokémon** (Charizard, Mewtwo, Terapagos, …): only the **default form's** stats are captured because `id="dex-stats"` is unique per HTML spec

